1. A point on the plane, **and**
2. Two **non-parallel** (i.e., not colinear) vectors lying on the plane (which can be used as direction vectors).

If you just have **two vectors**, we can treat them as direction vectors spanning the plane, but the actual plane equation needs a point. If you only have two vectors and no point, I can show how to represent the *directional span*, but not a full plane equation.

